        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:07PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 207 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Oliver Springs, or near Oak Ridge. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Ridge, Kingston, Oliver Springs, and Coalfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
